        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 9:09PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 909 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 6 miles north of San Jon to 13 miles
southeast of Ragland, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
San Jon, Grady, Wheatland, Broadview, Bellview and Bard.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 349 and 373.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
